73 SECTION 3.
74 Said chapter is further amended by adding new Code sections to read as follows:
75 "39-2-18.1.
76 (a) A blocked trust account required to be established by a child performer's parent or legal
77 guardian shall provide, at a minimum, that:
78 (1) Except as provided in Code Section 39-2-18.2, at least 15 percent of the gross
79 earnings of the child performer shall be deposited into the account;
80 (2) The funds in the account shall be available only to the child performer;
81 (3) The account shall be held by a trust company, as defined in Code Section 44-5-111;
82 (4) The funds in the account shall become available to the child performer when the
83 minor reaches the age of majority or is declared emancipated; and
84 (5) The account meets the requirements of Article 5 of Chapter 5 of Title 44, 'The
85 Georgia Transfers to Minors Act.'
86 (b) The child performer's parent or legal guardian shall provide the child performer's
87 employer with the information necessary to transfer funds into the blocked trust account.
88 Once such employer deposits funds into the account, such employer shall have no further
89 obligation or duty to monitor or account for such funds, and only the trustee shall be
90 obligated to monitor and account for such funds.
91 (c) If the child performer's parent or legal guardian fails to provide the child performer's
92 employer with the information necessary to transfer funds into the blocked trust account
93 within 30 days after the start of employment, funds that were to be transferred to the
94 account shall be reported and remitted to the state revenue commissioner in accordance
95 with Code Section 44-12-214 of the 'Disposition of Unclaimed Property Act.' The state
