98 39-2-18.2.
99 (a) A minor is considered engaged in the work of online content creation when the
100 following criteria are met at any time during the previous 12 month period:
101 (1) At least 30 percent of the online content creator's compensated video content
102 produced within a 30 day period included the likeness, name, or image of the minor.
103 Such content percentage is measured by the percentage of time the likeness, name, or
104 image of the minor visually appears or is the subject of an oral narrative in a video
105 segment as compared to the total length of the segment; and
106 (2) The number of views received per video segment on any online platform met the
107 online platform's threshold for the generation of compensation or the online content
108 creator received actual compensation for video content equal to or greater than 10Â¢ per
109 view.
110 (b) All online content creators whose content features a minor engaged in the work of
111 online content creation shall maintain the following records and shall provide such records
112 to the minor or such minor's parent or legal guardian on an ongoing basis:
113 (1) The name and documented proof of the age of the minor engaged in the work of
114 online content creation;
115 (2) The amount of content that generated compensation as provided for in subsection (a)
116 of this Code section during the reporting period;
117 (3) The total number of minutes of the content for which the online content creator
118 received compensation during the reporting period;
119 (4) The total number of minutes each minor was featured in content during the reporting
120 period;
