129 (d) A minor satisfying the criteria provided in subsection (a) of this Code section shall be
130 compensated by the online content creator. The online content creator shall set aside gross
131 earnings on the video content including the likeness, name, or image of the minor in a
132 blocked trust account according to the following distribution:
133 (1) When only one minor meets the content threshold described in subsection (a) of this
134 Code section, the percentage of total gross earnings on any video segment including the
135 likeness, name, or image of the minor that is equal to or greater than half of the content
136 percentage that includes the minor; or
137 (2) When more than one minor meets the content threshold described in subsection (a)
138 of this Code section and a video segment includes more than one such minor, the
139 percentage described in subsection (a) of this Code section for all minors in any segment
140 shall be equally divided between the minors, regardless of differences in percentage of
141 content provided by the individual minors.
142 (e) If an online content creator knowingly or recklessly violates the requirements provided
143 for in subsection (d) of this Code section, the minor or such minor's parent or legal
144 guardian may commence a civil action to enforce the provisions of such subsection. The
145 court may award to a minor who prevails in any action brought in accordance with this
146 Code section actual damages, punitive damages, and the costs of such action, including
147 attorney's fees and litigation costs.
